        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3847077642" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8162061305803631684"><i>Ach, said the old woman behind the wall. I&apos;m sick of all that Holocaust shit.</i><br/><br/>I do get where Auslander is coming from with this book (and it was really interesting to read about his background growing up in an Orthodox Jewish community), but I could not, for the life of me, get over how poorly it was written. It would go on like this. Sentences all broken off. Severed. Incredibly dull – though, yes, it is supposed to be a funny one. I&apos;ll admit I did skip a lot of it, as Auslander&apos;s point had alre</span>
  <span id="freeText8162061305803631684" style="display:none"><i>Ach, said the old woman behind the wall. I'm sick of all that Holocaust shit.</i><br /><br />I do get where Auslander is coming from with this book (and it was really interesting to read about his background growing up in an Orthodox Jewish community), but I could not, for the life of me, get over how poorly it was written. It would go on like this. Sentences all broken off. Severed. Incredibly dull – though, yes, it is supposed to be a funny one. I'll admit I did skip a lot of it, as Auslander's point had already been made in the first 15 pages or so.</span>
