<div id="review_341437684" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/341437684" />
    <a title="Hannah" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/865367-hannah"><img alt="Hannah" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/341437684?book_show_action=true">Jun 02, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Hannah" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Hannah" href="/user/show/865367-hannah">Hannah</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/865367-hannah?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/865367-hannah?shelf=jewish">jewish</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer341437684" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer119262435104376137">Shalom Auslander&apos;s first full-length novel takes a slight detour from his usual angst about Orthodoxy (see <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/50902.Foreskin_s_Lament' title='Foreskin&apos;s Lament by Shalom Auslander' rel='nofollow noopener'>Foreskin&apos;s Lament</a> and <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/50901.Beware_of_God_Stories' title='Beware of God Stories by Shalom Auslander' rel='nofollow noopener'>Beware of God: Stories</a>) to poke fun at gluten intolerance, muse about epitaphs and take Anne Frank off her historical pedestal by finding her alive and well (and old and curmudgeonly) in the attic of a bucolic farmhouse recently bought by a neurotic Jewish guy. What&apos;s not to like? <br/><br/>After a day of reflection, though, I think what&apos;s holding me back from a higher review is</span>
  <span id="freeText119262435104376137" style="display:none">Shalom Auslander's first full-length novel takes a slight detour from his usual angst about Orthodoxy (see <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/50902.Foreskin_s_Lament" title="Foreskin's Lament by Shalom Auslander" rel="nofollow noopener">Foreskin's Lament</a> and <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/50901.Beware_of_God_Stories" title="Beware of God Stories by Shalom Auslander" rel="nofollow noopener">Beware of God: Stories</a>) to poke fun at gluten intolerance, muse about epitaphs and take Anne Frank off her historical pedestal by finding her alive and well (and old and curmudgeonly) in the attic of a bucolic farmhouse recently bought by a neurotic Jewish guy. What's not to like? <br /><br />After a day of reflection, though, I think what's holding me back from a higher review is that Shalom Auslander is best suited to either full-length nonfiction or short fiction. Much as I enjoyed the premise, appreciated Auslander's wordcraft, and adored the characters, this felt a little stretched--it could easily have been half as long. It's a good read, to be sure, but I found myself getting impatient. <br /><br />Bill and Jennifer take note: this book is not about babies.</span>
  <a data-text-id="119262435104376137" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


